metadata.name: A Poem #17
metadata.description:
An abstract representation of a poem written with signs and ink drops. Inspiring heart and emotion, escaping the logic and rationale mind. Providing hints and indication of joy and love. 

This work, like all others, builds upon my constant research of recreating in the generative world the artistic gesture explored in the physical one: painting with a palette knife, with large brushes or dripping colours on the canvas.

- hit 'p' for .png export
- hit 's' for .svg export

metadata.description:
"To capture the fleeting time in the generating process."

In this work,I d'like focus on the generating of generative art system itself rather than imitate some scene or style.
And with the flow of time, try to figure out where it can take me toward.

This work would be a series of my alternative view on generative art.
"Œ±" means the first step of this series.

Press [s] in live view to save file as PNG.
Press [p] to stop.

metadata.name: Kalk Bay Beach #2
metadata.description:
This project is called Kalk Bay Beach. The initial idea of ‚Äã‚Äãthis collection came to my mind when I found the most beautiful place to live and the most hospitable people there. I strongly recommend you to visit kalk Bay Village in South Africa. .

Details of this collection:
This collection includes unique graphic images of the Atlantic ocean that are randomly combined with each other and create incredibly beautiful scenes. I tried to paint my emotions there.
Each photo frame and its placement changes. The shadows of the trees that shine into the room, the ambient light, the images and the composition of the objects inside the photo frame and the table, etc.

I tried to translate my emotions by  hand by digital painting there.
I dedicate this collection to Ilona
